---
const steps = [
  { num: '01', label: 'plan',    body: 'planner decomposes the goal into a graph of steps.' },
  { num: '02', label: 'act',     body: 'executor runs the next step on the graph.' },
  { num: '03', label: 'observe', body: 'knowledge manager watches the gap between intended and actual.' },
  { num: '04', label: 'replan',  body: 'planner folds what was learned into a revised graph.' },
];
---

<section id="plan-act" class="section">
  <div class="container-x">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[600px] text-center">
      <div class="eyebrow">the runtime loop</div>
      <h2 id="plan-act-headline" class="h-section mt-3">
        Plan, act, observe, <span class="hl">replan</span>.
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-5 max-w-[520px] text-fg-2" style="font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6;">
        When reality and the plan disagree — a tool failed, the data wasn’t what was expected, a new constraint surfaced — the plan changes mid-run.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ol class="mx-auto mt-12 grid max-w-[1080px] grid-cols-1 gap-3 md:grid-cols-[1fr_28px_1fr_28px_1fr_28px_1fr]">
      {steps.flatMap((step, i, arr) => [
        (
          <li class="rounded-[12px] border border-border-subtle bg-canvas p-5">
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
              <span class="font-mono text-fg-3" style="font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">{step.num}</span>
              <span class="font-mono text-fg-1" style="font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">{step.label}</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-fg-2" style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5;">{step.body}</p>
          </li>
        ),
        ...(i < arr.length - 1 ? [(
          <li class="hidden items-center justify-center md:flex" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="28" height="14" viewBox="0 0 28 14" fill="none" stroke="#111" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="opacity: 0.55;">
              <path d="M2 7 L 24 7"/>
              <path d="M19 2 L 26 7 L 19 12"/>
            </svg>
          </li>
        )] : []),
      ])}
    </ol>

    <div class="mx-auto mt-3 hidden max-w-[1080px] justify-center md:flex" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 320 40" width="100%" height="38" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet" fill="none" stroke="#111" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="opacity: 0.55;">
        <path d="M310 4 C 310 24, 290 32, 160 32 C 30 32, 10 24, 10 4" stroke-dasharray="3 4"/>
        <path d="M16 10 L 10 4 L 4 10"/>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-[520px] text-center font-mono text-fg-3" style="font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.04em;">
      the plan is a living document, not a script.
    </p>

    <div class="mx-auto mt-12 max-w-[640px] rounded-[14px] bg-sunken p-7">
      <div class="eyebrow">steering, mid-run</div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-fg-1" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.65;">
        You can intervene through the SDK too. Adjust the goal, add a constraint, hand the agent new context — the planner folds your steer into the next plan revision. The agent doesn’t restart. <span class="hl-soft">It updates.</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
